•
Remember to join my @timeless_jiujitsu FB group (link in bio) & check out my blog at www.TimelessJiuJitsu.com to be able to ask me questions & learn from me consistently. I drop a free technique video every Tuesday 🙌

Three years ago today, I earned my 4th first round MMA submission victory in one of the greatest nights of my MMA career. This Bellator event was held in Chicago, which is where my dad is from, & the card was headlined by the greats @fedoremelianenkoofficial & @thefrankmir. The inspiration level was extremely high!!!
•
Much respect to @geraldharris2 for stepping in as a last minute replacement. He had never been submitted in 30 fights & has some notorious slam KO’s, so I had to be sneaky & cautious while setting up this finish. Last year, Bellator rated this the number 1 submission in their history. You can watch the full submissions countdown video here - https://youtu.be/9XN7-AmQ3go

•
Join the class at www.TimelessJiuJitsu.com/webinar or join my Timeless Facebook group (link in bio) for all the info 👊

My friend @riccardoammendoliabjj did an awesome job breaking down my recent @f2wbjj main event Kimura victory on @flograppling! The knee cut pass straight to the Kimura has been one of my strongest finishing sequences for a long time. There are a lot of details involved & Riccardo did an excellent job of pointing out many of them. Some of the 🔑’s are recognizing their arm position as soon as you pass & making sure you grab the hand instead of the wrist when finishing the kimura 🔒

Last week I shared a video of me teaching this technique & how I set it up inside my Facebook group (link in bio 👊🏼) & I have compiled all my recent #TechniqueTuesday videos into my new TimelessJiu-Jitsu Blog. Check them out here: https://www.timelessjiujitsu.com/blog

Been swamped since returning home from Montana & finally have a moment to post about the incredible experience I had at my MMA retreat at @budokonuniversity Whitefish, Montana last week. Beautiful Montana summer plus teaching/training/moving 7-8hrs per day with an awesome group of students made for an amazing week!
•
I really enjoyed spending the week breaking down a little bit of my MMA game for the students. We worked Muay Thai, Grappling, & Striking into Takedowns & even though I had the challenge of teaching a couple of students with very little martial arts experience, because we were able to work everyday, they were able to put it all together very well by the end of the week. I was very pleased with everyone’s energy & focus during the training & am extremely grateful for the opportunity to share my craft & passion with them. I am very confident that they will be continuing their martial arts journey when they return to their homes. Big thanks to my brother @cameronshayne welcoming me to be a part of his Budokon training course & connecting martial arts to his movement teachings. Also, thanks to @melayneshayne, @kemba_quinn, & @chef_brunogallindo for all their work behind the scenes 🙏
•
Check out the young warrior @eden_._s from @cyborgbjj demonstrate one of the #LovatoStyle sequences we worked in the last slide 😁💪👊

What a big weekend for our @lovatobjjmma Children Warriors!!! Our first ever @ibjjf Pan Kids Champions @issathebeastabjj & @akindsavage 👏👏👏 These two have been there before & fell short. This year they worked harder than ever & achieved their goal showing beautiful Jiu-Jitsu along the way. Issa submitted all three of her opponents & Taylor won a tough first match & then got the sub in the finals & received her yellow belt on the podium Super proud & happy for these two!!!
•
We are also very proud of Mookie & Nora for earning bronze medals in their very first Kids Pan. Both had some tough matches & fought until the end. I know they will be back stronger than ever! Special recognition to Coaches @dylantaylor.n & @landonvon for being in their corner as well as Coach Josh, Prof @shilohrolls, & all the assistant coaches back home who help make our program so great! Also thanks to the parents who trust & support our work 🙏 @okc_kids_bjj

node.text: #TBT to Purple Belt years with my dad. This was 2000, a few years later we would become Black Belts. Who would’ve expected a father & son duo from Oklahoma, without a Black Belt instructor in their state, would have become the first American father & son Black Belts??? “It always seems impossible until it’s done.” ❤️🥋🇺🇸
